                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d339">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 652.119/207</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_SWG1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-11-15T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 15, 1917, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2816. Your 2722 November 12: Repeat to London for information of <persName
                        corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_MVC1">McCormick</persName>.</p>
                <p>Subject is so important Department is surprised that French Government has made
                    no representation. Representations have been made here in regard to importance
                    of Spanish commerce for Allies by individuals and by Spanish Ambassador.
                    Department asked French Government for information in regard to trade with
                    Spain, but have so far received no satisfactory reply. Suggest that you discuss
                    subject with French Government and keep Ambassador <persName
                        corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_WJE1">Willard</persName> informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
